"pressing return in 'read' menu will let you reading current file. this" b'program will automatically determine which format this file is.' b'the procedure is: first, check magic number. if fail, check' b'standard extension. still fail, report error.' b"pressing s or s in 'read' menu will do 'slide show'." b'if delay time is program will wait until you hit a key' b'(except escape).' b'if any error occurs, program will make a beep.' b'escape to terminate.' b"pressing ins in 'read' menu will change display type." b"pressing alt-x in 'read' menu will quit program without prompting." b'' b"2. once image file is successfully read, you will enter 'screen' menu." b'within this menu f5 is turn on. you can do special effect on image.' b'pressing return: show image.' b'in graphic mode, press return, space or escape to return to text' b'mode.' b'pressing tab: change processing target. this program allows you to do' b'special effects on 8-bit or 24-bit image.' b'pressing left,right arrow: change display type. bits.' b'pressing space: save current image to file.' b'b/w dither: save as black/white image(1 bit).' b'grey scale: save as grey image(8 bits).' b'full color: save as color image(8 bits).' b'true color: save as 24-bit image.' b'' b'this program will ask you some questions if you want to write image' b'to file. some questions are format-dependent. finally this program' b'will prompt you a filename. if you want to save file under another' b'directory other than current directory, please press space. after' b"pressing space, you will enter 'write2' menu. you can change" b'directory to what you want. then,' b'' b"pressing space: this program will prompt you 'original' filename." b"pressing return: this program will prompt you 'selected' filename" b'(filename under bar).' b'' b'' b'3. this program supports bits display.' b'' b"4. this program is memory greedy. if you don't have enough memory," b'the performance is poor.' b'' b'5. if you want to save bits image b'try gif then tiff(lzw) then targa then sun raster then bmp then b'' b'if you want to save bits image (lossless):' b'try tiff(lzw) or targa or ilbm or sun raster' b'(no one is better for true 24bits image)' b'' b'6. i recommend jpeg for storing bits images, even bits images.' b'' b'7. not all subroutines are fully tested' b'' b'8. this document is not well written. if you have any problem, suggestion,' b'comment about this program,' b'i need your suggestion to improve this program.' b'(there is no anonymous ftp on this site)' b'' b'' b'(8) tech. information:' b'program (user interface and some subroutines) written by jih-shin ho.' b'some subroutines are borrowed from xv(2.21) and pbmplus(dec b'tiff(v3.2) and jpeg(v4) reading/writing are through public domain' b'libraries.' b'compiled with djgpp.' b'you can get whole djgpp package from simtel20 or mirror sites.' b'for example, wuarchive.wustl.edu: /mirrors/msdos/djgpp' b'' b'' b'(9) for thoese who want to modify video driver:' b'1. get grx source code from simtel20 or mirror sites.' b'2. for hicolor and truecolor:' b'15 bits of colors is set to b'16 bits of colors is set to 0xc010.' b'24 bits of colors is set to 0xc018.' b'' b'' b'acknowledgment:' b'i would like to thank the authors of xv and pbmplus for their permission' b'to let me use their subroutines.' b'also i will thank the authors who write tiff and jpeg libraries.' b"thank dj. without djgpp i can't do any thing on pc." b'' b'' b'jih-shin ho' 